olive oil
1 pear
1 bag parsley
1 packet roasted almonds
10 g butter
1 bag salad leaves
1 drizzle balsamic glaze
2 radish
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

Slice the pear into thin wedges. Trim the radish and thinly slice. Roughly chop
the parsley leaves. Roughly chop the roasted almonds.

In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil and the butter over a medium
heat. Cook the pear in a single layer, turning occasionally, until softened,
8-10 minutes. Transfer to a bowl and set aside to cool slightly.

TIP: Save on washing up and combine everything in your serving bowl!

Add the radish and mixed salad leaves to the pear and toss to combine.
Season with salt and pepper.

Transfer the salad to a serving bowl. Top with the parsley, roasted almonds
and grated Parmesan cheese. Serve drizzled with some balsamic glaze.